{
  "texts": [
    "The lack of clear and comprehensive guidelines for data usage compounds the issue (Schnoes et al., 2009).",
    "Public domain data release protocols acknowledge the tension between unrestricted access and data producers desire for recognition through first publication rights.",
    "This conflict has led to multiple interpretations, fuelling an ongoing debate about how publicly available data should be used.",
    "The pressure to be the first to uncover significant discoveries can lead to data withholding until after publication, hindering broader dissemination (Tenopir et al., 2020).",
    "Even after publication, challenges persist, including time constraints in preparing data for sharing, legal and privacy considerations, and concerns about misinterpretation or misuse."
  ]
}